context: In June 2013, West and television personality <a4_0>Kim Kardashian<a4_0/> announced the birth of their first child, <a0_0><a5_0>North<a5_0/><a0_0/>. In October 2013, the couple announced their engagement to widespread media attention. November 2013, West stated that he was beginning work on his next studio album, hoping to release it by mid-2014, with production by Rick Rubin and Q-Tip. In December 2013, <a1_0>Adidas<a1_0/> announced the beginning of an official apparel collaboration with West, to be premiered the following year. In May 2014, West and Kardashian were married in a private ceremony in <a6_0>Florence<a6_0/>, Italy, with a variety of artists and celebrities in attendance. West released a single, "Only One", featuring <a2_0><a7_0>Paul McCartney<a7_0/><a2_0/>, on December 31, 2014. "FourFiveSeconds", a single jointly produced with Rihanna and McCartney, was released in January 2015. West also appeared on the Saturday Night Live 40th Anniversary Special, where he premiered a new song entitled "Wolves", featuring Sia Furler and fellow Chicago rapper, Vic Mensa. In February 2015, West premiered his clothing collaboration with Adidas, entitled <a8_0>Yeezy Season 1<a8_0/>, to generally positive reviews. This would include West's Yeezy Boost sneakers. In March 2015, West released the single "All Day" featuring Theophilus London, Allan Kingdom and Paul McCartney. West performed the song at the <a3_0>2015 BRIT Awards<a3_0/> with a number of US rappers and UK grime MC's including: Skepta, Wiley, Novelist, Fekky, Krept & Konan, Stormzy, Allan Kingdom, Theophilus London and Vic Mensa. He would premiere the second iteration of his clothing line, Yeezy Season 2, in September 2015 at New York Fashion Week.
